Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into wedges.

Cut half the @broccoli{1/2} (double for 4p) into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

Pop the chopped broccoli and onion onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{1%tsp}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until veg is tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Boil a large #pot{} of @water{to taste} for the @udon noodles{300%g}.

Add the noodles then lower heat to medium-high and cook until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot.

Drizzle with @oil{1%tsp} and stir through to stop them sticking together.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, place a large #pan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @sesame seeds{1%sachet} and lightly toast, stirring regularly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once toasted, transfer to a small #bowl{} and set aside.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{1%tsp}.

Add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%g}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fry until golden and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add @hoisin sauce{2%sachets}, @soy sauce{2%sachets}, garlic and 50ml water (double for 4p).

Lower heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a little water if needed.

When everything is ready, divide the noodles between your plates.

Top with the glazed chicken, roasted onion and broccoli.

Spoon over the remaining hoisin sauce from the pan.

Scatter over the toasted sesame seeds to finish.